{
  "stem": "1282.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this is why I have learned not to condemn the world or not even all the Germans, the guilty ones, because there was a woman, as we were marched through a small village.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She stood on the second floor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I could see her face now, an elderly woman, wrinkled face.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she had an apron up and stood against the window, which was open, and looked at us and looked.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And as we passed under the window, she dropped the apron.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And about 20 loaves of bread just rolled out from the window onto the floor, right on top of us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Well, of course, we jumped on top of each other and we devoured it and-- but the SS soldier was standing behind the corner on guard duty, aimed his machine shoe gun, shot her, and we saw her fall back.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Killed her.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was somewheres between Munich and Dachau.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Dachau is about 40, 50 kilometers from Munich.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was somewheres-- I knew it was a small community.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never knew which community we're going.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We've had several, several incidences which were just as horrible.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But these two have remained with me the rest of my life, because one was a question of my pledge, which I couldn't keep.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Another one was, do I condemn the rest of my life when this happened to me?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then eventually we wound up and we came in to Dachau, somewheres the third week of April or so.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in Dachau, the Germans were already approaching Munich at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know that they have heard about Dachau and they're preparing to liberate, which was the first camp that Americans liberated under Eisenhower.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the Germans wanted to destroy the whole camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
